====Usage notes====
In reference to temples, {{m-self|zh|宮}} is used for {{w|Chinese folk religion|traditional deities}} considered to rank highly in the celestial bureaucracy, such as {{w|Mazu}} who was honored by the {{w|Qing dynasty}} as the "Queen of Heaven" after their successful {{w|Qing conquest of Taiwan|invasion of Taiwan}}. In earlier history, it also referred to {{w|ancestor worship|ancestral}} shrines.

